                                <div class="asset-content entry-content">

                                    <div class="asset-body">
                                        Dear Washington State,<br /><br />Last year, consumer rights activists lost a campaign in California to label foods containing GMOs. We were stunned by this outcome. <br /><br />Highly respected members of our society, including <a href="http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/blog/dr-oz-applauds-whole-foods-market-gmo-labeling">Dr. Oz</a> and <a href="http://www.mnn.com/your-home/organic-farming-gardening/stories/anti-gm-crop-petition-tops-million-signatures">Greenpeace</a>, believe that GMOs should be labeled or banned altogether. Bizarrely, Californians rejected their sound advice and instead sided with the American Medical Association and the American Association for the Advancement of Science. Apparently, these alleged "<a href="http://articles.latimes.com/2012/jun/21/news/la-heb-gmo-foods-medical-association-20120620">doctors</a>" and "<a href="http://www.aaas.org/news/releases/2012/1025gm_statement.shtml">scientists</a>" think GMO food labels are a bad idea. Whatever.<br /><br /><img alt="children-GMO-300.jpg" src="http://www.realclearscience.com/blog/children-GMO-300.jpg" class="mt-image-right" style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px;" height="280" width="327" />But, good news. We haven't given up! This November, the citizens of Washington State (possibly including a handful of <a href="http://www.seattlepi.com/local/article/Dead-voted-in-governor-s-race-1163612.php">dead</a> or <a href="http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2003808207_votefraud27m.html">imaginary</a> citizens, too) will vote on Initiative 522. If it passes, Washington will become the first state to require labels on foods containing GMOs.<br /><br />We know that if any state can do this, it will be you, Washington. We know that you pride yourself on being progressive and forward-thinking. In fact, you're so enlightened, that you have one of the highest <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm6230a3.htm">vaccine refusal rates</a> in the country. Bravo! Instead of poisoning your children with unnatural chemicals that probably cause autism, you'd rather take your chances with pertussis and measles. We respect that.<br /><br />Because of your common sense rejection of vaccines, we know that you will also protect your food supply from this unnatural contamination known as "genetic modification." And do be sure to use the word "contamination" as often as possible. It evokes emotive images of infectious disease and pus-filled wounds. It's the perfect word to manipulate those unfamiliar with biotechnology.<br /><br />So onward, Washingtonians! The people of your state have the <i>right to know</i> what's in their food! <br /><br />But, please don't get too carried away with this "right to know" campaign, as the consequences could be dire. If organic food was forced to carry a label, the public might find out <a href="http://blogs.scientificamerican.com/science-sushi/2011/07/18/mythbusting-101-organic-farming-conventional-agriculture/">all sorts of things they won't like</a>. For instance, organic farmers use pesticides, some of which, like rotenone, might be dangerous. And since healthy lifestyles and environmentalism are popular in your state, your citizens might be distressed to find out that organic food is neither more nutritious nor more environmentally friendly than conventional food. <br /><br />After all, consumers might have the right to know, but they certainly don't need to know everything.<br /><br />Sincerely,<br /><br />An Enlightened Anti-GMO Activist<br /><br />(<a href="http://now.msn.com/facebook-censors-monsanto-protest-photos-of-children-with-anti-gmo-signs">Photo</a>: Facebook)<br />



<div style="margin-top:10px;height:15px" class="zemanta-pixie"><a class="zemanta-pixie-a" href="http://www.zemanta.com/?px" title="Enhanced by Zemanta"><img style="border:none;float:right" class="zemanta-pixie-img" src="http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=91c400e7-6324-4177-90fa-4f5954e598d9" alt="Enhanced by Zemanta" /></a></div>
                                    </div>


                                </div>
                                <div class="asset-footer">

    


                                    <div class="entry-tags">
                                        <h4>Tags<span class="delimiter">:</span></h4>
